es of 24. It&#39;s probably my second favorite card game ever so far but I&#39;m a huge fan of the show. I did quit stargate. There is no support for it and everything I heard at comicon points to no more expansions and their just milking this new set online and in real life to make a little $$$$ of it. I plan on 24 being my last TCG ever and 2 or 10 expansions I hope it will stay just as fun. But I am a TCG addict. I like playing them against an opponent. I just don&#39;t like videogames. They are way to impersonal and I ussually only play them for the stories if they seem interesting. <br><BR><font size=1>02:46 10-20-2007</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>CategoryOneGame</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor='#FFFFFF' ><font class="bfont">Mike - I&#39;d like to hear your story with FMA.  I talked to a playtester and I flat out asked him if the Movie set was going to be made and he said just watch and see and a smile face meening to me that it would.<br />
